    "body": "Exceptions should always get instantiated immediately when raising them. Trying to instantiate them in the potentially very different context when they are being handled or even during intermediate processing bares substantially more risks of failure and can lead to unpredictable results.\n\nThis has been discussed on the mailing list:\n\nhttp://thread.gmane.org/gmane.comp.python.cython.devel/13283\n\nMigrated from http://trac.cython.org/ticket/788",
    "closed_at": "2012-08-30T09:01:04Z",
